# Host-level Caddy reverse proxy for the word-address app.
#
# Caddy runs on the host (not in compose) and terminates TLS, proxying the two
# public domains to the compose services bound on 127.0.0.1. Domains come from
# the environment ({$FRONTEND_DOMAIN} / {$API_DOMAIN}) so nothing is hardcoded.
#
# Provide them however you run Caddy, e.g.:
#   export FRONTEND_DOMAIN=address.example.com
#   export API_DOMAIN=api.example.com
#   caddy run --config ./Caddyfile
# (or set them in the caddy.service systemd unit). Caddy provisions HTTPS certs
# automatically for the named domains.

{$FRONTEND_DOMAIN} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}

{$API_DOMAIN} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
